Defendant Jerry A. Williams in court.  Attorney Michael C Griesbach in court for Jerry A. Williams. Attorney Marconi De Franca Barros in court for State of Wisconsin. 
State moves to delete the repeater enhancers in count 2, count 7 and count 8.  Motion granted.
NO CONTEST to the amended charge in count 2, felony bail jumping.  Convicted.
NO CONTEST to the amended charge in count 7, disorderly conduct.  Convicted.
NO CONTEST to the amended charge in count 8, resisting/obstructing an officer.  Convicted.
State moves to dismiss and read in counts 1 and 3-6.  Motion granted.
Sentence withheld and defendant is placed on probation to DOC for two (2) years.  
Conditions of probation:
1) Assessment, treatment, counseling as deemed appropriate by the Departments assessment process;
2) Have no assaultive contact with C.W.   (Agent may place further restrictions at his/her discretion) 
3) Maintain absolute sobriety with the exception of any prescription medications;
4) Maintain fulltime employment, schooling, work search or combination;
5) Pay court costs;
6) Pay supervision fees in an amount to be determined by DOC;
7) Provide DNA sample
8) Submit to random urine screens and pay for same.
